description:
Running following query from ISQL console
SPARQL define output:format "JSON"
define sql:signal-void-variables 1

SELECT DISTINCT ?floorCount
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://ruian.linked.opendata.cz/sparql> {
     <https://ruian.linked.opendata.cz/zdroj/stavební-objekty/22088181> <https://ruian.linked.opendata.cz/slovník/početPodlaží> ?floorCount
  }
}
gives me an empty result.
However, running the same query via JDBC driver gives me the following output
{
   "head":{
      "link":[],
      "vars":[
         "floorCount"
      ]
   },
   "results":{
      "distinct":false,
      "ordered":true,
      "bindings":[
         {
            "floorCount":{
               "type":"typed-literal",
               "datatype":"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer",
               "value":"1"
            }
         }
      ]
   }
}

The floorCount is suddenly 1 however running mentioned query on target HTTP SPARQL Endpoint https://linked.opendata.cz/sparql gives me an empty result. This can be also verified via running DESCRIBE <https://ruian.linked.opendata.cz/zdroj/stavební-objekty/22088181>.
Running mentioned query via local SPARQL HTTP Endpoint yields to no matches.
But probably due to issue reported in #1026.
Running the query from ISQL yields to same result - no matches.
